{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "easyvtc-planning-revenues-sprint6",
    "name": "EasyVTC API — Planning & Revenus (Sprint 6)",
    "description": "# EasyVTC — Module Planning & Revenus Chauffeur\n\n## Endpoints couverts\n\n### Chauffeur (self)\n- `GET /drivers/me/planning`             → Son planning hebdo ou mensuel\n- `GET /drivers/me/revenues`             → Ses revenus (semaine / mois / tout)\n\n### Admin / Manager\n- `GET /admin/drivers/:id/planning`      → Planning d'un chauffeur spécifique\n- `GET /admin/drivers/:id/revenues`      → Revenus d'un chauffeur spécifique\n\n## Paramètres communs\n| Query param | Valeurs           | Défaut  |\n|-------------|-------------------|---------|\n| `period`    | `week` \\| `month` \\| `all` (revenus seulement) | `week` (planning) / `month` (revenus) |\n| `date`      | `YYYY-MM-DD`      | Aujourd'hui |\n\n## Structure de la réponse — Planning\n```json\n{\n  \"ok\": true,\n  \"data\": {\n    \"period\": \"week\",\n    \"date_from\": \"2026-06-01T00:00:00.000Z\",\n    \"date_to\": \"2026-06-07T23:59:59.999Z\",\n    \"total\": 3,\n    \"reservations\": [\n      {\n        \"id\": \"uuid\",\n        \"status\": \"assigned\",\n        \"scheduled_at\": \"2026-06-02T09:00:00Z\",\n        \"pickup_address\": \"12 rue de Rivoli\",\n        \"dest_address\": \"Aéroport CDG T2\",\n        \"vehicle_type\": \"berline\",\n        \"price_estimated\": 78,\n        \"price_final\": null,\n        \"country\": \"france\",\n        \"client\": { \"first_name\": \"Marie\", \"last_name\": \"Martin\", \"phone\": \"+33600000002\" },\n        \"trip\": null\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## Structure de la réponse — Revenus\n```json\n{\n  \"ok\": true,\n  \"data\": {\n    \"period\": \"month\",\n    \"date_from\": \"2026-06-01T00:00:00.000Z\",\n    \"date_to\": \"2026-06-30T23:59:59.999Z\",\n    \"total_trips\": 12,\n    \"total_revenue\": 624.50,\n    \"currency\": \"EUR\",\n    \"revenue_by_currency\": { \"EUR\": 624.50, \"XOF\": 0 },\n    \"trips\": [\n      {\n        \"reservation_id\": \"uuid\",\n        \"scheduled_at\": \"2026-06-15T10:00:00Z\",\n        \"pickup_address\": \"Gare de Lyon\",\n        \"dest_address\": \"Orly T4\",\n        \"price_final\": 62,\n        \"currency\": \"EUR\"\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## Prérequis\n1. Lancer l'API : `npm run dev` (port 4000)\n2. Avoir en base : un compte driver avec profil `drivers` validé (status = active)\n3. Avoir des réservations assignées/terminées liées à ce driver\n\n## Ordre d'exécution recommandé\n1. 🔐 Setup — Tokens\n2. 🔍 Setup — IDs\n3. 📅 Chauffeur — Planning\n4. 💰 Chauffeur — Revenus\n5. 👨‍💼 Admin — Planning par driver ID\n6. 👨‍💼 Admin — Revenus par driver ID\n7. 🔒 Contrôle d'accès\n\n## Variables sauvegardées automatiquement\n- `driver_token`, `admin_token`\n- `driver_id` (drivers.id — PK de la table drivers, pas le user_id)",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "base_url",     "value": "http://localhost:4000", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "driver_token", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "admin_token",  "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "driver_id",    "value": "", "type": "string" }
  ],
  "item": [

    {
      "name": "🔐 Setup — Tokens",
      "description": "Connexion Driver et Admin. Les tokens sont sauvegardés en variables de collection.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Login Driver",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/login", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["auth", "login"] },
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"driver@test.com\",\n  \"password\": \"Driver1234!\"\n}" }
          },
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
            "pm.test('driver_token sauvegardé', () => {",
            "  const { ok, data } = pm.response.json();",
            "  pm.expect(ok).to.be.true;",
            "  pm.collectionVariables.set('driver_token', data.access_token);",
            "  console.log('driver_token OK — user_id:', data.user?.id);",
            "});"
          ]}}]
        },
        {
          "name": "Login Admin",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/login", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["auth", "login"] },
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"admin@test.com\",\n  \"password\": \"Admin1234!\"\n}" }
          },
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
            "pm.test('admin_token sauvegardé', () => {",
            "  const { ok, data } = pm.response.json();",
            "  pm.expect(ok).to.be.true;",
            "  pm.collectionVariables.set('admin_token', data.access_token);",
            "  console.log('admin_token OK');",
            "});"
          ]}}]
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "name": "🔍 Setup — IDs (driver_id)",
      "description": "Récupère le driver_id (PK de la table drivers) nécessaire pour les routes admin.\n⚠️ Ne pas confondre avec user_id — c'est bien l'ID de la table `drivers`.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET /admin/drivers — récupérer driver_id",
          "description": "Sauvegarde l'id du premier chauffeur retourné (drivers.id, pas user_id).\nSi votre driver de test n'est pas en tête de liste, entrez driver_id manuellement dans les variables de collection.",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{admin_token}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/admin/drivers?status=active&limit=10",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["admin", "drivers"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "status", "value": "active" },
                { "key": "limit",  "value": "10" }
              ]
            }
          },
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
            "pm.test('driver_id sauvegardé', () => {",
            "  const { ok, data } = pm.response.json();",
            "  pm.expect(ok).to.be.true;",
            "  const list = data.drivers ?? data.data ?? (Array.isArray(data) ? data : []);",
            "  if (Array.isArray(list) && list.length > 0) {",
            "    const d = list[0];",
            "    pm.collectionVariables.set('driver_id', d.id);",
            "    console.log('driver_id (drivers.id):', d.id, '|', d.user?.first_name, d.user?.last_name);",
            "  } else {",
            "    console.warn('⚠️ Aucun chauffeur actif — saisir driver_id manuellement dans les variables de collection');",
            "  }",
            "});"
          ]}}]
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /drivers/me — vérifier profil chauffeur connecté",
          "description": "Vérifie que le driver_token correspond bien à un chauffeur avec un profil drivers existant.",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{driver_token}}" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/drivers/me", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["drivers", "me"] }
          },
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
            "pm.test('Profil chauffeur valide', () => {",
            "  const { ok, data } = pm.response.json();",
            "  pm.expect(ok).to.be.true;",
            "  pm.expect(data.id).to.be.a('string');",
            "  pm.expect(data.user).to.be.an('object');",
            "  if (!pm.collectionVariables.get('driver_id')) {",
            "    pm.collectionVariables.set('driver_id', data.id);",
            "  }",
            "  console.log('Driver:', data.user?.first_name, data.user?.last_name, '| status:', data.status, '| zone:', data.zone);",
            "});"
          ]}}]
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "name": "📅 Chauffeur — Planning (self)",
      "description": "GET /drivers/me/planning\nLe chauffeur consulte son propre planning. Les courses annulées sont exclues.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "[Driver] GET planning — semaine courante (défaut)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{driver_token}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/drivers/me/planning",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["drivers", "me", "planning"]
            }
          },
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
            "pm.test('Structure planning correcte', () => {",
            "  const { ok, data } = pm.response.json();",
            "  pm.expect(ok).to.be.true;",
            "  pm.expect(data.period).to.equal('week');",
            "  pm.expect(data.date_from).to.be.a('string');",
            "  pm.expect(data.date_to).to.be.a('string');",
            "  pm.expect(data.total).to.be.a('number');",
            "  pm.expect(data.reservations).to.be.an('array');",
            "  pm.expect(data.reservations.length).to.equal(data.total);",
            "  console.log('Semaine:', data.date_from?.slice(0,10), '→', data.date_to?.slice(0,10), '| courses:', data.total);",
            "});",
            "pm.test('Aucune réservation annulée', () => {",
            "  const { data } = pm.response.json();",
            "  const hasCancelled = data.reservations.some(r => r.status === 'cancelled');",
            "  pm.expect(hasCancelled).to.be.false;",
            "});",
            "pm.test('Chaque réservation a les champs attendus', () => {",
            "  const { data } = pm.response.json();",
            "  if (data.reservations.length > 0) {",
            "    const r = data.reservations[0];",
            "    ['id','status','scheduled_at','pickup_address','dest_address','vehicle_type',",
            "     'price_estimated','price_final','country','client','trip'].forEach(k => {",
            "      pm.expect(r, `champ manquant: ${k}`).to.have.property(k);",
            "    });",
            "    if (r.client) {",
            "      pm.expect(r.client).to.have.property('first_name');",
            "      pm.expect(r.client).to.have.property('last_name');",
            "    }",
            "  }",
            "});",
            "pm.test('Réservations triées par scheduled_at ASC', () => {",
            "  const { data } = pm.response.json();",
            "  if (data.reservations.length >= 2) {",
            "    const t1 = new Date(data.reservations[0].scheduled_at).getTime();",
            "    const t2 = new Date(data.reservations[1].scheduled_at).getTime();",
            "    pm.expect(t1).to.be.at.most(t2);",
            "  }",
            "});"
          ]}}]
        },
        {
          "name": "[Driver] GET planning — semaine spécifique (2026-06-09)",
          "description": "Le 9 juin 2026 est un mardi → semaine du lundi 8 juin au dimanche 14 juin.",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [{ "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{driver_token}}" }],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/drivers/me/planning?period=week&date=2026-06-09",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["drivers", "me", "planning"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "period", "value": "week" },
                { "key": "date",   "value": "2026-06-09" }
              ]
            }
          },
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "exec": [
            "pm.test('Status 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
            "pm.test('Semaine lundi→dimanche correcte', () => {",
            "  const { ok, data } = pm.response.json();",
            "  pm.expect(ok).to.be.true;",
            "  pm.expect(data.period).to.equal('week');",
            "  // Lundi 8 juin 2026",
            "  pm.expect(data.date_from).to.include('2026-06-08');",
